The paper presents an algorithm for obtaining an optimal control policy for hybrid dynamical systems in cluttered environments, which involves trajectory optimization and obstacle avoidance. This problem setting is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including robotics (cs.RO), control systems (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
